# General Rules - ArchivistMCP

## Project Context

**ArchivistMCP** — Kotlin MCP server for document indexing with ChromaDB.

- **Type**: Model Context Protocol Server (MCP)
- **Transport**: STDIO + SSE
- **Purpose**: Semantic indexing and search of documents (PDF, TXT, MD)

## Tech Stack

| Component | Version |
|-----------|---------|
| Kotlin | 2.2.21 |
| Ktor | 3.3.3 |
| MCP Kotlin SDK | 0.11.1 |
| ChromaDB | embedded |
| Gradle | 9.4.1 |

## Structure

```
src/main/kotlin/io/modelcontextprotocol/sample/server/
├── server.kt       # Main MCP server
├── main.kt        # Entry point
├── chroma/        # ChromaDB client
├── documents/      # Document parsing
├── indexing/      # Indexing logic
└── tools/         # MCP tools
```

## Commands

```bash
./gradlew build      # Build project
./gradlew run       # Run server
./gradlew test     # Run tests
./gradlew shadowJar # Create uber-jar
```

## Rules

1. Always use Gradle for building
2. Use sealed class for result types
3. Use suspend functions with Dispatchers.IO
4. Use snake_case for MCP tools
5. ChromaDB in embedded mode, storage in `./data/chromadb`